1. To compile the program "New_Alarm_Cond.c", use the following command:
   
   make
   
2. To run the executable code, use the following command:
   
   ./New_Alarm_Cond
   
3. At the prompt, type in the number of seconds at which the alarm should
   expire, followed by Message(n), where n is the message number, and the
   text of the message.
   
   For example:
   
   5 Message(2) Good Morning!
   
   (To exit from the program, type Ctrl+D.)
   
4. To read the output from the testing procedures, use the following command:
    
   cat Test_output
